abstract: The plan would raise an estimated $5 trillion in new revenue from corporations and wealthy Americans, but it is significantly less aggressive than many other candidates’ plans.
snippet: The plan would raise an estimated $5 trillion in new revenue from corporations and wealthy Americans, but it is significantly less aggressive than many other candidates’ plans.
lead_paragraph: While most of the Democratic field barnstormed Iowa on Saturday, former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York, who is not competing in the state, released a tax plan from afar.
headline_main: Bloomberg, far from Iowa, releases a tax plan.

abstract: Two billionaire Democratic presidential hopefuls, Michael Bloomberg and Tom Steyer, collectively spent about $389 million last year on their campaigns, more than the rest of the remaining Democratic field combined, according to disclosures filed on Friday.
snippet: Two billionaire Democratic presidential hopefuls, Michael Bloomberg and Tom Steyer, collectively spent about $389 million last year on their campaigns, more than the rest of the remaining Democratic field combined, according to disclosures filed o...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two billionaire Democratic presidential hopefuls, Michael Bloomberg and Tom Steyer, collectively spent about $389 million last year on their campaigns, more than the rest of the remaining Democratic field combined, according to disclosures filed on Friday.
headline_main: Billionaires Bombard U.S. Presidential Campaign With Hundreds of Millions in Cash
headline_print_headline: Billionaires Bombard U.S. Presidential Campaign With Hundreds of Millions in Cash

abstract: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
snippet: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bail...
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
headline_main: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey
headline_print_headline: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey

abstract: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."

headline_main: A front-row seat at Elizabeth Warren’s rally.

abstract: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
snippet: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Democratic National Committee released its latest debate qualification criteria on Friday, and as is tradition, some candidates think they’re unfair.
headline_main: Democrats criticize D.N.C. change to debate rules.

abstract: Ms. Warren kicked off her final blitz of campaign events Saturday afternoon, pitching herself as a candidate who can unite the Democratic Party’s moderate and progressive factions.
snippet: Ms. Warren kicked off her final blitz of campaign events Saturday afternoon, pitching herself as a candidate who can unite the Democratic Party’s moderate and progressive factions.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS — Senator Elizabeth Warren kicked off her final blitz of campaign events Saturday afternoon, pitching herself as a candidate who can unite the Democratic Party’s moderate and progressive factions.

abstract: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
snippet: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — As excellent as the Bernie Sanders event was — as excellent as it was to hear from the filmmaker Michael Moore and to eat Ben & Jerry’s ice cream scooped by the actual Ben and the actual Jerry, longtime Sanders supporters — it would have been even more excellent, was the general feeling, if Mr. Sanders himself had been able to come to Ottumwa.

abstract: With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.
headline_main: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech
headline_print_headline: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech
